 SSH -secured shell
  used for authentication
  by setting we can connect to gitlab without username and password
  
  setting ssh key
  -----------------
cmd- $ ssh-keygen
path-enter
enter
goto gitlab->settings-> ssh keys ->contents of id-rsa.pub file in the path and add key
verify ssh key is added
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

gitlab runner
-------------------
gitlab runner is used to run jobs and send results back to GitLab

-setting gitlabrunner
installation
create a new folder and paste the downloded file and rename  
git dash run as adm->go to folder location
run cmd -> gitlab-runner.exe install
to check version ->gitlab-runner --version

-register gitlab(process to bind runner with gitlab instatnce)
to register gitlab-runner.exe register
enter
tokken will be in gitlab account( in project ->settings->cicd->runners-> set up a sepcific runner manually
gitlad ci tags
eg;-ssh, ci

-start 
gitlab-runner.exe start //to start
gitlab-runner.exe stop //to stop runner



 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 
benefits of using GitLab for CI/CD
 ->use a single tool from planning to deployment
 ->run distributed jobs on separate machines
 -> run jobs in parallel on multiple machines
 -> make use of optimized delivery

